Blastomere.label: Blastomere
Blastomere.description: In biology, a blastomere is a type of cell produced by cleavage of the zygote after fertilization and is an essential part of blastula formation. Wikipedia

Blastopore.label: Blastopore
Blastopore.description: A blastopore is an opening into the archenteron during the embryonic stages of an organism. The distinction between protostomes and deuterostomes is based on the direction in which the mouth develops in relation to the blastopore. Wikipedia

Blastula.label: Blastula
Blastula.description: The blastula is a hollow sphere of cells, referred to as blastomeres, surrounding an inner fluid-filled cavity called the blastocoele formed during an early stage of embryonic development in animals. Wikipedia

Embryo.label: Embryo
Embryo.description: An embryo is a multicellular diploid eukaryote in its earliest stage of development, from the time of first cell division until birth, hatching, or germination. Wikipedia

Placenta.label: Placenta
Placenta.description: The placenta is an organ that connects the developing fetus to the uterine wall to allow nutrient uptake, waste elimination, and gas exchange via the mother's blood supply. Wikipedia

Zygote.label: Zygote
Zygote.description: A zygote, is the initial cell formed when two gamete cells are joined by means of sexual reproduction. In multicellular organisms, it is the earliest developmental stage of the embryo. Wikipedia

Inner cell mass.label: Inner cell mass
Inner cell mass.description: In early embryogenesis of most eutherian mammals, the inner cell mass is the mass of cells inside the primordial embryo that will eventually give rise to the definitive structures of the fetus. Wikipedia

Alar plate.label: Alar plate
Alar plate.description: The alar plate is a neural structure in the embryonic nervous system, part of the dorsal side of neural tube, that involves the communication of general somatic and general visceral sensory impulses. Wikipedia

Morula.label: Morula
Morula.description:
A morula is an embryo at an early stage of embryonic development, consisting of cells in a solid ball contained within the zona pellucida.
The morula is produced by embryonic cleavage, the division of the zygote. Wikipedia

Amniotic cavity.label: Amniotic cavity
Amniotic cavity.description: The amniotic cavity is the closed sac between the embryo and the amnion, containing the amniotic fluid. Wikipedia

Bilaminar blastocyst.label: Bilaminar blastocyst
Bilaminar blastocyst.description: Bilaminar blastocyst or Bilaminar disc refers to the epiblast and the hypoblast, evolved from the embryoblast. These two layers are sandwiched between two balloons the primitive yolk sac and the amniotic cavity. Wikipedia

Blastocoele.label: Blastocoele
Blastocoele.description:
A blastocoel or blastocele is the fluid-filled central region of a blastula and mammalian blastocyst. A blastocoele forms during embryogenesis when a zygote divides into many cells through mitosis.
The adjectival of "blastocoel" is blastocoelic. Wikipedia

Cloacal membrane.label: Cloacal membrane
Cloacal membrane.description:
The cloacal membrane is the membrane that covers the embryonic cloaca when still in the development of the urinary and reproductive organs.
It is formed by ectoderm and endoderm coming into contact with each other. Wikipedia
